               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360201-name-1179" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1179" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1179" type="surname" value="BROOKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360201-name-1179" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BROOKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Wenworth-buildings, East-road. About a quarter before six o'clock in the evening of the 4th of February, I was passing along Finsbury-pavement, Moorfields—I put my hand to my pocket and missed my handkerchief—I looked round and saw the prisoner six or seven yards off, in the road, drawing it under his coat—it blew into the road—this is it—I collared him and gave him into custody.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner</hi>. It was not in my possession at all.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. I saw it in his possession—I did not see him drop it—he was drawing it under his coat, and looking at me at the same time—there were two others found on him.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183602010206"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
